  "prompt": "Who is Bruce Wayne?",
  "response": "Bruce Wayne is a fictional character and the secret identity of the superhero Batman, created by artist Bob Kane and writer Bill Finger. He first appeared in \"Detective Comics\" #27 in 1939. As the wealthy owner of Wayne Enterprises, Bruce Wayne is a prominent and influential figure in Gotham City. After witnessing the murder of his parents, Thomas and Martha Wayne, during a robbery when he was a child, he vows to fight crime and protect the city.\n\nTo achieve this goal, Bruce trains extensively in various forms of martial arts, detective skills, and physical conditioning. He uses advanced technology, gadgets, and his intellect while donning the Batman persona, allowing him to combat villains such as the Joker, Catwoman, the Riddler, and others. Batman operates primarily at night and utilizes fear as a weapon against criminals, often relying on his iconic bat-themed costume and symbolism.\n\nThe character of Bruce Wayne/Batman has become an enduring and iconic figure in popular culture, appearing in numerous comic books, animated series, television shows, and live-action films.",
